1
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Roş baş temaşevanên me yên hêja!
 
Good day, our dear viewers!

2
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Ji kanala Hevhatin a Efrînê silavên me pir ji we re hene.
 
Many greetings to you from Afrin's Hevhatin channel.

3
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Şev û rojên we rehet bin, em bi kêf in.
 
May your nights and days be comfortable, we are happy.

4
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Em vegeriyan gel we bi xelekeke nû, xelekekî me îro jî cuda
ye,
 
We have returned to you with a new episode, our episode
today is also different,

5
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,000
ji ber ku em li gundî me ne, gundê Çemo.
 
because we are in our village, the village of Çemo.

6
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Bi rastî hemî gundên Efrînê xweş in, lê gundê dayîkbûna
mirov, baştir e.
 
In truth, all the villages of Afrin are beautiful, but the
village of one's birth is better.

7
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Em bi Efrînkî dibêjin, kes navê mastê xwe tirş e. Em jî
navên mastê xwe tirş e.
 
In Afrin dialect we say, nobody calls their own yogurt sour.
We also don't call our yogurt sour.

8
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Belê temaşevanên me yên hêja, îro ez û Zîn û xwişka Hêv, em
ê derbasî gundê Çemo bin.
 
Yes our dear viewers, today Zîn, sister Hêv, and I will
enter the village of Çemo.

9
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Em ê niha li gundê Çemo bin, em ê nav gund bigerin.
 
We will now be in the village of Çemo, we will wander
through the village.

10
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Hewaldorên li gundê Çemo şikeft pir ne.
 
There are many caves around the village of Çemo.

11
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

12
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:38,000
Du salan carekê cejna Newroz li gundê Çemo çêdibû.
 
Every two years, the Newroz festival used to take place in
the village of Çemo.

13
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

14
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:41,000
Gundê Çemo li navçeya Şera ye.
 
The village of Çemo is in the Şera district.

15
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Em ê pir tiştan di vê vîdeoyê de zanibin.
 
We will learn a lot of things in this video.

16
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:50,000
Em ê derbasî cem xwedanê xwe bin, em ê silavên xwe bidin, em
ê seke kesên di vê gundî de dimînin çawa jiyan dikin.
 
We will visit our people, we will give our greetings, we
will see how the people living in this village live.

17
00:01:50,000 --> 00:02:10,000
Bê noha jî bi me ra bin, em ê bi hev ra derbasî gundê Çemo
bin.
 
Stay with us now, we will enter the village of Çemo
together.

18
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Belê temaşevanên me yên hêja wek ku hûn dibînin em derbasî
gundê Çemo bûn.
 
Yes our dear viewers, as you can see, we have entered the
village of Çemo.

19
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Ji gundê Çemo jî em herî taybet derbasî vê malbatê dibin.
 
From the village of Çemo, we are specifically visiting this
family.

20
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:41,000
Vê malbatê re dibêjin mala Îbisê Elî Hêwê, Ebû Ekrem.
 
This family is called the family of Îbisê Elî Hêwê, Abu
Akram.

21
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Em ê derbasî cem gundiyan bin, em ê çîrokên wan bibîhîsin.
 
We will visit the villagers, we will hear their stories.

22
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:48,000
Em ê pir meselan bi hev ra xeber din.
 
We will talk about many things together.

23
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:53,000
Belê temaşevanên me yên hêja, berî em derbasî vê malbatê
dibin, ez dixwazim çîçkekî jî we ra li ser gundê Çemo deng
kim.
 
Yes our dear viewers, before we visit this family, I want to
talk a little bit to you about the village of Çemo.

24
00:02:53,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Gundê Çemo pir kevnar e. Pir şikeft tê de hene, pir cihên
dîrokî tê de hene.
 
The village of Çemo is very ancient. It has many caves and
many historical sites.

25
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Pir bîr tê de hene.
 
It has many wells in it.

26
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:06,000
Belê wek dibêjin çîrokên gund dibêjin, wek me re hatiye
xeberdan,
 
Yes, as the village stories tell, as it was told to us,

27
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:17,000
Navê gundê Çemo bi esil, ji piraniya çemo tê de hene,
piraniya kaniyan, nav lê kirin Çem. Nav lê hatiye kirin Çem.
 
The name of the village of Çemo originally, because of the
many rivers in it, the many springs, they named it Çem. It
was named Çem.

28
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:22,000
Û gund jî, wek dî, du salan Newroz li gundê Çemo çêdibû.
 
And as for the village, as you saw, for two years Newroz was
held in the village of Çemo.

29
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:29,000
Xanima mamoste Ednan Dilbirîn, Xwedê rehma xwe lê ke, ew jî
di vir da ye. Ew jî ji gundê Çemo ye.
 
The wife of teacher Ednan Dilbirîn, may God have mercy on
him, she is also from here. She is also from the village of
Çemo.

30
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:35,000
Bi mere bin... Em ê hîn bêtir... çîrokên gundê Çemo nas
bikin û em ê noha dest bi xeleka xwe bikin.
 
Stay with us... We will get to know even more stories of the
village of Çemo and we will now start our episode.

31
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Silav.
 
Greetings.

32
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Sibeha we bi xêr.
 
Good morning.

33
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,000
Ya we jî silamet be.
 
May yours be peaceful too.

34
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:44,000
Berî her tiştî em bixwazin spasiya we bikin, mal û halê xwe
ji me ra vekiriye, em mîvandar in li gundê Çemo.
 
First of all, we want to thank you, you opened your home and
life to us, we are guests in the village of Çemo.

35
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Ser serî me ser çavên me.
 
You are very welcome (on my head, on my eyes).

36
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:49,000
Saetên we xweş xaltî. Tu çawa yî, tenduristiya te çawa ye?
 
Have a good time, aunt. How are you, how is your health?

37
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,000
Hemdullah, şukur, xweş e. Tu çawa yî dayê?
 
Praise be to God, thanks, it's good. How are you, mother?

38
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,000
Ê şevên Çemo çawa ne? Şêrîn in?
 
How are the nights of Çemo? Are they sweet?

39
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,000
Pir şêrîn in.
 
Very sweet.

40
00:03:54,000 --> 00:04:02,000
Belê temaşevanên me yên hêja, wek ku hûn dibînin, her weha
em li gundî ne, li gundê me jî em li cem malbatê me ne.
 
Yes our dear viewers, as you can see, as we are in the
village, in our village we are also with our family.

41
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,000
Ve kesên ku em pê re rûniştine, malbatê me ne.
 
These people we are sitting with are our family.

42
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Metkên min in, metka min e, û dayîka min e.
 
They are my aunts, my aunt, and my mother.

43
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:12,000
Metka min e, dayîka min e.
 
It's my aunt, my mother.

44
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:15,000
Noha jî em ê bi hev ra zanibin, ka ew çi tiştî di vir ra
çêdikin.
 
Now we will find out together, what they are making here.

45
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:22,000
Ev şîva ku çêdikin. Ji dema ez çûçik bûm ve, ez zanim metkên
min vê şîveyê dikin û gundê Çemo vê şîveyê dikin.
 
This dish they are making. Since I was a child I know my
aunts make this dish and the village of Çemo makes this
dish.

46
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:25,000
Xwişka Metê... ji min re xeber de, ev şorbeya zehterê ye.
 
Sister Metê... tell me about it, this is thyme soup.

47
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:28,000
Li her gundekî pê re dibêjin tiştekî, lê nexasim gundê Çemo
ekterî pê çêdikin.
 
In every village they call it something, but especially the
village of Çemo mostly makes it.

48
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:32,000
Ekterî gundê Çemo bi vê şîveyê meşhûr in, ev şîveyê biharê
ye.
 
Mostly the village of Çemo is famous for this dish, this is
a spring dish.

49
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

50
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:36,000
Bes zehterê dikinê? Zehter û dan û nîsk.
 
Do they only put thyme in it? Thyme, wheat, and lentils.

51
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Noha ku ji min re xeber de, we zehterê xwe ji ku anî ne?
 
Now tell me, where did you get your thyme from?

52
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,000
Me ji çiya aniye.
 
We brought it from the mountain.

53
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,000
Em li viderê dan dibînin.
 
We see wheat here.

54
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,000
Tebe'en ev yê malê ne.
 
Of course these are homemade.

55
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,000
Û dew yê malê ye.
 
And the ayran is homemade.

56
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:48,000
Em ê dewê xwe deynin ser ê, wê bikelînin. Em ê danê xwe
berdinê.
 
We will put our ayran on the fire, boil it. We will add our
wheat to it.

57
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:52,000
Talî em ê zehterê xwe têkin. Tiştek nakeve nav xeynî zehterê
û bes.
 
Finally we will add our thyme to it. Nothing else goes into
it except thyme, and that's it.

58
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:57,000
Ez dixwazim... ji min re xeber dî, ev xwarin li gundê we
tiştekî adet e?
 
I want you to tell me, is this dish a tradition in your
village?

59
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:00,000
Em ji deykên xwe hîn bûn. Û dêkên min jî... ji dêkên xwe hîn
bûn.
 
We learned it from our mothers. And my mother also...
learned it from her mother.

60
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:02,000
Tiştek yanî, ji kal û bavan... sedsalan.
 
So it's something, meaning, from ancestors... for centuries.

61
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:03,000
Cîl werê cîl...
 
Generation after generation...

62
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Û hemî xanimên gundê Çemo vê xwarinê çêdikin?
 
And do all the ladies of the village of Çemo make this dish?

63
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:09,000
Erê... gişt çêdikin. Mal bi mal çêdikin.
 
Yes... all of them make it. House by house, they make it.

64
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:13,000
Îro jî em û kesên li me temaşe dikin, bi hev ra em ê
zanibin... şorbeya zehterê çawa tê çêkirin.
 
Today too, we and those watching us, together we will
know... how thyme soup is made.

65
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:33,000
Erê temam.
 
Yes, okay.

66
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:53,000
Metê te çi xeber da?
 
Aunt, what did you say?

67
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:56,000
Em ê noha, dewê xwe berdinê...
 
We will now pour in our ayran...

68
00:05:56,000 --> 00:06:05,000
Heta ku dewê me bikele, em ê danê xwe têkin.
 
Once our ayran boils, we will add our wheat.

69
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,000
Em dihejînin manê, neqete.
 
We stir it so it doesn't curdle.

70
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:16,000
Eywa... manê neqete. Hêj mastê miyan be, em nahejînin pir.
Bes mastê çêlan be tê mecbûrî bihejînî.
 
Yes... so it doesn't curdle. If it's sheep's yogurt, we
don't stir it much. But if it's cow's yogurt, you are forced
to stir it.

71
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,000
Manê neqete.
 
So it doesn't curdle.

72
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,000
Manê neqete.
 
So it doesn't curdle.

73
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,000
Avê jî, li serê em dikinê?
 
Water, do we add it on top?

74
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:24,000
Avê, pişt re em ava digermînin.
 
Water, afterwards we heat some water.

75
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:31,000
Em ê tevdin... heta noha dikele... heta ku bikele em ê danê
xwe têkin.
 
We will stir it... until it boils now... once it boils, we
will add our wheat.

76
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:34,000
Paşî em ê xwêya xwe têkin, zehterê xwe têkin.
 
Then we will add our salt, and add our thyme.

77
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,000
Bes xwê têr dike fiyê?
 
Does just salt suffice for this?

78
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:38,000
Erê, bes xwê têr dike... û zehterê hişk yî.
 
Yes, just salt is enough... and dry thyme.

79
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:42,000
Şorbeya biharê... Şorbeya zehterê.
 
Spring soup... Thyme soup.

80
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:49,000
Şorbeya biharê, şorbeya zehterê...
 
Spring soup, thyme soup...

81
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:55,000
Metê berê tiştek hebû, we pê digerand, dest pê digirt.
 
Aunt, in the past there was something, you used it to stir,
you held it.

82
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Ew çemçiyê dar bû.
 
That was a wooden spoon.

83
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,000
Çemçiyê dar.
 
Wooden spoon.

84
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:07,000
Pê dew dihejandin. Nema, ew tişt rê çû. Nema.
 
They used to stir ayran with it. It's gone, those things are
gone. Gone.

85
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:15,000
Ecep emrê vê şîveyê teqrîben çiqas sal e? Ev evwel yeka vê
şîveyê pir kevn dibe.
 
I wonder, the age of this dish is approximately how many
years? This first one of this dish must be very old.

86
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:19,000
Ewel yek carê nizanim, bes aniha ji berê de dikin.
 
The first one, I don't know at all, but now, they have been
doing it since the past.

87
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:28,000
Ji berê de ev şîve heye... Bes di biharê zehter çêdibû, û
xelk çêdike... hefteyê carekê.
 
This dish has been around since the past... Just in spring,
thyme grows, and people make it... once a week.

88
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Noha em dibînin dewê me kelî...
 
Now we see our ayran has boiled...

89
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,000
Vê emrê min jî çil û şeş e na?
 
And my age is forty-six, right?

90
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,000
Tu jî çil û şeş sal in, na?
 
You are forty-six years old, right?

91
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:39,000
Çil û... Dayîka min jî dikir, emrê wê jî, heştê û...
 
Forty... And my mother used to make it, her age is also
eighty...

92
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,000
Nêzîkî not salan dikirin.
 
For nearly ninety years they were making it.

93
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:48,000
Sal dikirin... teqrîben emrê wê şîveyê... ser sed salan re
heye.
 
They made it for years... approximately the age of this
dish... is over a hundred years.

94
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:51,000
Hîn dadeyê ji dadeya xwe girtiye...
 
The mother still learned it from her mother...

95
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:54,000
Dor bi dor dihat.
 
Generation to generation.

96
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:57,000
Çîl da çîl...
 
Generation to generation...

97
00:07:57,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Her çîlekî, da dest cîlekî...
 
Every generation handed it to a generation...

98
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:05,000
Bes... ev kewn û manî mîras bimîne. Û xwarina xweş e.
 
But... this is ancient and remains a heritage. And it's a
delicious food.

99
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:08,000
Gelek şîveyên me dî... Gelek cureyên xwarinan hene ku em
tenê dizanin.
 
Many of our other dishes... There are many types of dishes
that only we know.

100
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:11,000
Pir şîve hene?
 
Are there many dishes?

101
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:16,000
Pir şîve hene... em şîveyek dikin... li ba me ekmeqaşî...
 
There are many dishes... we make a dish... with us it's
ekmeqaşî...

102
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,000
Ekmeqaşê hûn dikin?
 
You make ekmeqaşî?

103
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:23,000
Ew bi kurdî... Ew bi kurdî lê bi esasî navê wê bi tirkî
ye...
 
That is in Kurdish... It is in Kurdish, but basically its
name is in Turkish...

104
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:28,000
Ji bo navlêkirina gund e, û derdor gişt... tirkî daxil e.
 
It's because of the village's naming, and all the
surroundings... Turkish is included.

105
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:31,000
Navên wan şîvan, mesela boranî ye, dîsa şîveyek tirkî ye.
 
The names of those dishes, for example borani, is again a
Turkish dish.

106
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:39,000
Ekmeqaşî ye, bacanê sor e, dikelînin... sîr û pîvaz dikinê,
û nanê hişk dikinê û didin ser.
 
Ekmeqaşî is tomatoes, they boil them... they put garlic and
onion in it, and they put dry bread in it and put it on top.

107
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:42,000
Ew ekmeqaşiya çemoyî ye, ew jî meşhûr e.
 
That's the ekmeqaşî of Çemo, that's also famous.

108
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:52,000
Berê jî dew.
 
Earlier, also ayran.

109
00:08:52,000 --> 00:09:07,000
Hava nekelî... bikel, bikel, bikel, bikel, bikel...
 
This didn't boil... boil, boil, boil, boil, boil...

110
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:12,000
De be, da bi ser wan da. Dê jî bi ser min da.
 
Come on, turn it towards them. Turn it towards me too.

111
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:15,000
Tê bî...
 
It will come...

112
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:21,000
Wê nanê jî gundiyan bi piranî cem cemaetê çêdikirin?
 
Did the villagers also mostly bake that bread together in
the community?

113
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:27,000
Hemî li cem hev rûdiniştin.
 
They all sat together.

114
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:36,000
Metê çîçkekî weha bike... te xwar ke.
 
Aunt, do a little bit like this... tilt it.

115
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:42,000
Berê di gundên de, da ku çûn kaniyê... tiştên xwe bi devê
kaniyê dişûştin û dihatin?
 
In the past in the villages, when they went to the spring...
did they wash their things at the spring and come back?

116
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,000
Paşê bûbûn kûn...
 
Then they were worn out...

117
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:50,000
Paşê bûn kûn... û plastîkî bûn. Belê, ev meselaya jî, nema
bîra dî... ez jî ewqasî mezin nînim.
 
Then they became worn... and they were plastic. Yes, this
matter, I don't remember anymore... I'm not that old either.

118
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:57,000
Ew meselaya jî nema bîra we tî... her wekî derfetek e, da
xelk li nav gund... destê hev digirtin û çêdikirin.
Mesela... gund diçû kaniyê, paşê li malan belav dikirin.
 
You don't remember that matter anymore... just like it was
an opportunity, so people in the village... held each
other's hands and made things. For example... the village
went to the spring, then they distributed to the houses.

119
00:09:57,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Saet deh radibûn...
 
At ten o'clock they used to wake up...

120
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:03,000
Naha jî em hatin ava gundê Çamo, kaniya avê, kaniya gund.
 
Now we have reached the water of Çamo village, the water
spring, the village spring.

121
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:07,000
Yek ji selef kaniyan e, ev kaniya ku...
 
It is one of the old springs, this spring that...

122
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:10,000
Berê jî av jê dikişand.
 
Used to draw water before too.

123
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:13,000
Em ê bipirsin bê berê çawa dikişand û niha çawa dikişîne.
 
We will ask how they used to draw water and how they draw it
now.

124
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:19,000
Ev gundê me ne; Baro, Omer, Xatûn û hinek gundiyên din jî li
vir in.
 
These are our villagers; Baro, Omer, Xatûn and some other
villagers are also here.

125
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:24,000
Ev xalê min e... ez ê pirs bikim.
 
This is my uncle... I will ask him.

126
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:27,000
Tu çawa yî xalo, baş î? ... Tu bi xêr hatî.
 
How are you uncle, are you well? ... Welcome.

127
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:33,000
Berê tu dikarî ji me re behs bikî ku we çawa av ji vê bîrê
derdixist?
 
Could you tell us how you used to extract water from this
well in the past?

128
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:37,000
Berê teqrîben pêncî sal berê... me bi destan av derdixist.
 
In the past, about fifty years ago... we extracted water by
hand.

129
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:41,000
Lê niha, ev der kete bin xizmeta dewletê...
 
But now, this place has come under the service of the
state...

130
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:45,000
Dema berê çend gundiyên me du heb bûn...
 
In the past, a few of our villagers were two...

131
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:49,000
Niha bi saya şoreşê me sê înç av kişandiye.
 
Now, thanks to the revolution, we have extracted three
inches of water.

132
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:54,000
Çend bîrên me yên din jî hene, em sê înç me av lê dîtiye, li
vir jî sê înç e.
 
We have a few other wells where we have found three inches
of water, and here too it is three inches.

133
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:59,000
Me sê înç av kişand û niha em dikarin hîn zêdetir avê
bikşînin.
 
We extracted three inches of water and now we can extract
even more water.

134
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:04,000
Lê av hişk bû, me pompeyên sê înç lê daxistin.
 
But the water dried up, we lowered three-inch pumps into it.

135
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:10,000
Û niha, ev kar bi vî rengî berdewam e, em spasiya Xwedê
dikin.
 
And now, this work continues in this way, we thank God.

136
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:18,000
Heta niha jî bi saya me, elhemdulillah, av heye,
elhemdulillah em jê razî ne.
 
Until now, thanks to us, thank God, there is water, thank
God we are satisfied with it.

137
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:26,000
Niha hûn zîraetê dikin, hûn çi difroşin? Mînak zeytûnan, we
zeytûn difirotin?
 
Now you do agriculture, what do you sell? For example,
olives, did you sell olives?

138
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:31,000
Berê genim, ceh...
 
In the past, wheat, barley...

139
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:36,000
Gelek genim, ceh û nîsk, ev tişt hebûn.
 
A lot of wheat, barley and lentils, these things existed.

140
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:43,000
Li derdorê tiştekî din tune bû, lê paşê me darên zeytûnan
çandin.
 
There was nothing else around, but later we planted olive
trees.

141
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:48,000
Niha piraniya xelkê van deran zeytûnan datînin.
 
Now most of the people around here plant olives.

142
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:53,000
Van zeytûnan datînin, fêkiyan datînin.
 
They plant these olives, they plant fruits.

143
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:59,000
Li her derî em van tiştan dikin, inşallah em ê pêşve bibin.
 
We do these things everywhere, hopefully we will develop.

144
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:04,000
Darên hinarê, sêv, ev dar inşallah em ê çêkin.
 
Pomegranate trees, apple trees, we will hopefully plant
these trees.

145
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:07,000
De em biçin em ê kel û pelan bînin, em ê biçin bar bikin.
 
Let's go and bring the goods, we will go and load them.

146
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:11,000
Tîp ser navê we da da, de bînin.
 
Put the type on your name, come on bring it.

147
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:14,000
Me nanê xwe di nav de çêkir, paşê em ê...
 
We made our bread in it, then we will...

148
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:18,000
We ev dît... ka ev çi ye...
 
You saw this... what is this...

149
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:22,000
Ev...
 
This...

150
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:42,000
Em ê paşê tiştan têkin nav û piştî wê em ê amade bikin.
 
We will then put things inside and after that we will
prepare it.

151
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:58,000
Ev nêzik e... ka we çawa wilo kir?
 
This is close... how did you do it like that?

152
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:06,000
Çi çêdikin, xaltîkê? Ka ez bêjim, ew çi ye?
 
What are they making, aunt? Let me say, what is that?

153
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:10,000
Niha em şîvê dixwin. Em ê xilas bikin, piştî wê em ê nan
çêbikin.
 
Now we are eating dinner. We will finish, after that we will
make bread.

154
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:15,000
Te dît, ev... baş e...
 
You saw, this... okay...

155
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:20,000
Ev nanê me ye, te dît...
 
This is our bread, you saw...

156
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:25,000
Tu dibînî? ... Belê...
 
Do you see? ... Yes...

157
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:45,000
Ev şîva me ye.
 
This is our dinner.

158
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:52,000
Xalo, çima gundê we dibêjin Çamo? Navê gund Çamo ye, çima
Çamo?
 
Uncle, why do they call your village Çamo? The village's
name is Çamo, why Çamo?

159
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:57,000
Çamo, dema berê gundek hebû... gundekî piçûk... kaniyên avê
tê de hebûn.
 
Çamo, in the past there was a village... a small village...
there were water springs in it.

160
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:03,000
Kaniyeke mezin hebû. Ev her du gund teqasî 170 mal bûn, paşê
bûn du gund.
 
There was a large spring. These two villages were about 170
houses, then they became two villages.

161
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:09,000
Pênc-şeş mal di gund de mabûn. Berê malên me di gund de
bûn...
 
Five or six houses were left in the village. Previously our
houses were in the village...

162
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:15,000
Lê paşê em çûn derveyî gund û me malên xwe li derve ava
kirin.
 
But then we went outside the village and built our houses
outside.

163
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:22,000
Wê demê mirov kêm bûn, ji gund tenê pênc mal man.
 
At that time there were few people, only five houses
remained from the village.

164
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:28,000
Paşê mirov zêde bûn, hinek çûn bajar, hinek çûn deverên din.
 
Then the people multiplied, some went to the city, some went
to other places.

165
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:35,000
Di wê demê de malbatek hebû, gelek zarokên wan çêbûn û
malbat mezin bûn.
 
At that time there was a family, they had many children and
the families grew.

166
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:43,000
Wê demê kesî tiştek nedikir. Hemû malbat ketin nava vî halî.
 
At that time no one did anything. All the families fell into
this situation.

167
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:48,000
Paşê her malbat bû dehe mal.
 
Then each family became ten houses.

168
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:54,000
Pişt re sedsal an jî heştê mal ava bûn.
 
Then a century or eighty houses were built.

169
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:59,000
Em nizanin ka ev gund kîjan demê hatiye avakirin.
 
We don't know when this village was built.

170
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:04,000
Lê niha, gelê herêmê di ziraetê de kar dikin.
 
But now, the local people work in agriculture.

171
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:11,000
Berê, dema ez ciwan bûm, genim û ceh, gelek fêkî û sebze
hebûn.
 
Before, when I was young, there was wheat and barley, a lot
of fruits and vegetables.

172
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:16,000
Di van salên dawî de gelek tişt hatin guhertin.
 
In recent years many things have changed.

173
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:23,000
Inşallah di pêşerojê de em ê careke din wek berê pêşbikevin.
 
God willing, in the future we will develop again like
before.

174
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:29,000
Niha her tişt baş e. Dibe ku em gundekî nû jî ava bikin.
 
Everything is fine now. Maybe we will build a new village.

175
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:34,000
Ez nizanim, dibe ku ev gund dîsa mezin bibe.
 
I don't know, maybe this village will grow again.

176
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:39,000
Ev qas e... her malbat dê mezin bibe, em ê li gund bimînin.
 
This is it... every family will grow, we will stay in the
village.

177
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:45,000
Dê gelek malên din werin avakirin. Em hemû li vê derê ne.
 
Many more houses will be built. We are all here.

178
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:50,000
Xalo... tu dikarî ji me re bêjî ku ew kîjan malbatan bûn ku
çûn dervayî gund?
 
Uncle... can you tell us which families they were that went
outside the village?

179
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:56,000
Wan malbatan berê mala xwe çêkir û paşê hêdî hêdî ji gund
derketin.
 
Those families built their houses before and then slowly
left the village.

180
00:16:56,000 --> 00:17:01,000
Yanî malbatek li vir bû, yek li derveyî gund bû. Mînak
malbata Mamed, malbata...
 
So one family was here, one was outside the village. For
example, Mamed's family, the family...

181
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:08,000
Malbata Nasir û hinek malbatên din, ew jî gundekî mezin bûn,
selef bûn.
 
Nasir's family and some other families, they were also a big
village, they were ancestors.

182
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:15,000
Ev malbat hemû ji gund derketin û gundên nû ava kirin.
 
These families all left the village and built new villages.

183
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:22,000
Dema em piçûk bûn, em çend mal bûn û em li dora gund
digeriyan.
 
When we were small, we were a few families and we wandered
around the village.

184
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:29,000
Lê niha elhemdulillah, gelek tişt çêbûn, me her tişt baş
kir.
 
But now thank God, many things happened, we made everything
good.

185
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:37,000
Ez difikirim ku niha teqrîben du sed an sê sed mal hene li
van gundan.
 
I think there are approximately two hundred or three hundred
houses in these villages now.

186
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:44,000
Ez naxwazim rastiya wê bêjim, lê her yek bûye gundekî mezin.
 
I don't want to say the truth of it, but each one has become
a big village.

187
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:51,000
Belkî sê sed û pêncî mal, an zêdetir... lê gelek mirov ketin
van gundan.
 
Maybe three hundred and fifty houses, or more... but many
people entered these villages.

188
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:58,000
Di destpêkê de ew gundên biçûk bûn. Lê bi demê re mezin bûn.
 
In the beginning they were small villages. But over time
they grew.

189
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:03,000
Baş e, tu dikarî behsa berê bikî? Mînak li gund tiştekî din
hebû?
 
Okay, can you talk about the past? For example, was there
anything else in the village?

190
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:09,000
Dema berê dareke laleyê hebû, navê wê "Dara Lale" bû.
 
In the past there was a tulip tree, its name was "Dara
Lale".

191
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:14,000
Lê niha çend sal berê ew dar hate birîn.
 
But now a few years ago that tree was cut down.

192
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:21,000
Ez nizanim çima hat birîn, lê di nav gund de gelek dar
hebûn.
 
I don't know why it was cut down, but there were many trees
in the village.

193
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:29,000
Me nizanibû... em nêzîkî hefteyekê bêdar man, belê maşallah.
 
We didn't know... we were without trees for almost a week,
yes mashallah.

194
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:34,000
Niha ev dar in, li nav gund de cihê wan hene.
 
Now these are the trees, they have places in the village.

195
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:42,000
Lê hin dar hebûn ku deh, panzdeh sal berê hatin birîn.
 
But there were some trees that were cut down ten, fifteen
years ago.

196
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:49,000
Û ev camiya me ye... ev camiya gundî ye ku tê de nimêj
dikin.
 
And this is our mosque... this is the village mosque where
they pray.

197
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:55,000
Ev gelê vî gundî bi komkî alîkarî kir û ev camî çêkir.
 
The people of this village collectively helped and built
this mosque.

198
00:18:55,000 --> 00:19:02,000
Ji wan hinek pere kom kirin û camî ava kirin. Xwedê xêra wan
qebûl bike.
 
Some of them collected money and built the mosque. May God
accept their good deeds.

199
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:08,000
Ew kesên ku alîkarî kirin, înşallah dê cîhê wan cinet be.
 
Those who helped, God willing their place will be heaven.

200
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:14,000
Wan ev camî ava kir û ev yek bi destê wan çêbû.
 
They built this mosque and this was done by their hands.

201
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:20,000
Bi rastî, gelê me ji xêrê re her dem amade ye.
 
Indeed, our people are always ready for good deeds.

202
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:27,000
Ev gund e... û wek ku min got, em jê razî ne.
 
This is the village... and as I said, we are satisfied with
it.

203
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:34,000
Hûn dibêjin ku dema ev camî hate avakirin, gel bi hev re
alîkarî kirin.
 
You say that when this mosque was built, the people helped
together.

204
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:40,000
Belê, gava ku me camî çêkir, herkesî alîkarî kir. Hinekî zêr
da, hinekî...
 
Yes, when we built the mosque, everyone helped. Some gave
gold, some...

205
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:50,000
Yên ku tiştekî wan tune bû, bi karkirinê alîkarî kirin.
 
Those who had nothing, helped by working.

206
00:19:50,000 --> 00:20:00,000
Ez ketime xerîbiyê, bê te sebra min nayê...
 
I have fallen into foreign lands, without you I have no
patience...

207
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:05,000
Eşqa te pir giran e, yarê nikam hilgirim.
 
Your love is very heavy, my love, I cannot carry it.

208
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:11,000
Lê lê yarê, lê yarê, rinda te kulîlkê biharê.
 
Oh my love, oh my love, your beauty is a spring flower.

209
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:18,000
Destê xwe bide destê min da, herin çiyayê Hawarê.
 
Put your hand in my hand, let's go to Mount Hawar.

210
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:24,000
Lê lê yarê, lê yarê, rinda te kulîlkê biharê.
 
