211
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:44,000
Destê xwe bide destê min da, herin çiyayê Hawarê.
 
Put your hand in my hand, let's go to Mount Hawar.

212
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:07,000
Belê temaşevanên me yê hêja, em noka li gundê Çema ne.
 
Yes our dear viewers, we are now in Çema village.

213
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:13,000
Gundê Çema, li navçeya Şera dikeve, nêzîkî sê kîlometre ji
navçeya Şera dûr dikeve.
 
Çema village is located in the Şera district, it is about
three kilometers away from the Şera district.

214
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:17,000
Nêzîkî bîst kîlometre ji kantona Efrînê dûr dikeve.
 
It is about twenty kilometers away from the Afrin canton.

215
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:25,000
Cîranên gundê Çema, gundê Sînka ye, gundê Qerqîna ye, gundê
Be'raş e, gundê Omera ye.
 
The neighbors of Çema village are Sînka village, Qerqîna
village, Be'raş village, and Omera village.

216
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:30,000
Belê, pir zikak di vî gundî de hene, pir şikeft di vî gundî
de hene.
 
Yes, there are many alleys in this village, there are many
caves in this village.

217
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:32,000
Pir cihên turasî di vî gundî de hene.
 
There are many heritage sites in this village.

218
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:37,000
Wek Xirab Sîman, wek Xirabî Şefaqê, wek Kaniya Sîman.
 
Like Xirab Sîman, like Xirabî Şefaqê, like Kaniya Sîman.

219
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:40,000
Û hîn pir tiştên din hene.
 
And there are many other things too.

220
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:43,000
Camiyek vî gundî yek e, dibistan li vî gundî yek e.
 
This village has one mosque, and this village has one
school.

221
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:51,000
Bes heta refa şeşê di vî gundî de dixwînin, wekî din
xwendekarên vî gundî diherin navçeyê dixwînin, navçeya Şera.
 
But they only study up to the sixth grade in this village,
otherwise the students of this village go to study in the
district, the Şera district.

222
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:55,000
Tixtorê vî gundî hene, xwendevanên vî gundî hene, muhamî li
vî gundî hene.
 
This village has doctors, this village has students, this
village has lawyers.

223
00:21:55,000 --> 00:22:01,000
Tê dûr e ez te nabînim, ez nexweş im nabim rabe.
 
You are far away, I cannot see you, I am sick, I cannot get
up.

224
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:05,000
Eşqa te pir giran e, yarê nikam hilgirim.
 
Your love is very heavy, my love, I cannot carry it.

225
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:13,000
Eşqa te pir giran e, rindê nikam hilgirim.
 
Your love is very heavy, beautiful one, I cannot carry it.

226
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:16,000
Lê lê yarê lê yarê...
 
Oh my love, oh my love...

227
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:22,000
Û bi giştî piraniya ciwanên vî gundî karê terzîniyê dikin,
terzî ne.
 
And generally, most of the youth of this village do
tailoring work, they are tailors.

228
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:30,000
Ê di Helebê de dixebitin, ê li firna ye, ê li Efrînê, lê
belê kesên gund de dijîn, debara jiyana xwe bi çandiniyê,
 
Some work in Aleppo, some in bakeries, some in Afrin, but
those who live in the village make a living from farming,

229
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:34,000
Û bi xwedîkirina heywana dikin.
 
And by raising animals.

230
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:37,000
Erdê xwe hene cot dikin, rezên xwe hene.
 
They have their land which they plow, they have their
vineyards.

231
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:41,000
Deşta vî gundî heye, berî vî deştê sêv bûn, çeftelî bûn.
 
This village has a plain, the produce of this plain used to
be apples, peaches.

232
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:46,000
Û her we tiştê li ser Çema zanim ez bi xwe ji vî gundî me.
 
And whatever I know about Çema, I myself am from this
village.

233
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:52,000
Ez dixwazim hûn ji min re yazî bikin, her kes ji kîjan gundî
ye? Her kes dixwaze em li kîjan gundî teswîr bikin?
 
I want you to write to me, which village is everyone from?
Which village does everyone want us to film in?

234
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:54,000
Emê derbasî wî gundî bin jî.
 
We will go into that village too.

235
00:22:54,000 --> 00:23:00,000
Gerek hûn gundê xwe bîr nekin, û hûn bi gundê xwe serbilind
bin, ez jî bi gundê xwe pir serbilind im.
 
You shouldn't forget your village, and you should be proud
of your village, I am very proud of my village too.

236
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:06,000
Lê lê yarê lê yarê, rinda te gul û bihar e.
 
Oh my love, oh my love, your beauty is a spring flower.

237
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:11,000
Destê xwe bide destê min da, herin çiyayê Hawarê.
 
Put your hand in my hand, let's go to Mount Hawar.

238
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:16,000
Lê lê yarê lê yarê, rinda te gul û bihar e.
 
Oh my love, oh my love, your beauty is a spring flower.

239
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:36,000
Destê xwe bide destê min da, herin çiyayê Hawarê.
 
Put your hand in my hand, let's go to Mount Hawar.

240
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:55,000
Belê, belê temaşevanên me yê hêja, em noka jî li gund li bin
darekê ne, ev dar li destpêka Çema ye, yanî li ewelî Çema
ye.
 
Yes, yes our dear viewers, we are now also under a tree in
the village, this tree is at the beginning of Çema, meaning
at the entrance of Çema.

241
00:23:55,000 --> 00:24:00,000
Bi vê darê re dibên Dara Lalê, me dixwest em çîroka vê darê
jî bibîsin, lê me nas nekiriye.
 
They call this tree the Mute's Tree, we wanted to hear the
story of this tree too, but we haven't found out.

242
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:05,000
Da erê ta gelo kî çandiye, nav lal bû, lê zeman da nav lal
lêkirin.
 
Well, who planted it, was the name mute, or did they name it
mute over time.

243
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:12,000
Çîroka wê jî me nizanî. Em bi hêvî ne kî çîroka vê darê zane
ji me re di ta'lîqata de bike.
 
We didn't know its story either. We hope whoever knows the
story of this tree will write it for us in the comments.

244
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:16,000
Tiştek heye min bîr kir ewî re di xeleka xwe de bizikirînim.
 
There is something I forgot to mention to you in my episode.

245
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:24,000
Di Çema de avayê Rişko, avayekî pir navdar e.
 
In Çema, the Rişko dance style is a very famous style.

246
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:30,000
Heta niha ciwanên Çema bi vê avayî di daweta, di van
